# .dev.vars - Cloudflare Worker Development Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .dev.vars and fill in your actual values
# This file is git-ignored for security

# ===== REQUIRED VARIABLES =====

# Anthropic API Key for Claude Code functionality
# Get this from: https://console.anthropic.com/
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-your-anthropic-api-key-here

# ===== OPTIONAL VARIABLES =====

# GitHub App ID (can be set via config endpoint instead)
# This is the numeric ID of your GitHub App
# GITHUB_APP_ID=123456

# GitHub Webhook Secret (can be set via config endpoint instead)
# This is the secret you set when creating the GitHub App webhook
# GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret_here

# Development Environment Override
# This overrides the default environment setting
# ENVIRONMENT=development

# ===== DEBUG & LOGGING =====

# Enable debug logging (optional)
# DEBUG=*

# Log level for development (optional)
# LOG_LEVEL=debug

# ===== DEVELOPMENT SETTINGS =====

# Development mode flag (optional)
# DEV_MODE=true

# Local development port override (optional)
# DEV_PORT=8788

# ===== SECURITY SETTINGS =====

# Skip webhook signature verification in development (NOT RECOMMENDED)
# Only use for local testing with mock webhooks
# SKIP_WEBHOOK_VERIFICATION=false

# ===== NOTES =====
# 
# 1. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is the only required variable
# 2. GitHub App credentials can be set via the /config API endpoint
# 3. This file should NEVER be committed to version control
# 4. For production, set variables in Cloudflare Workers dashboard
# 5. Environment variables here are available in the Worker runtime
# 6. Container environment variables are passed through the MyContainer class